<textBlocks>
	<container id="formVBox">
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="25.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="Participatory Social Vulnerability Assessment Activity">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="In this activity you will engage members of the community in locating hazards and assets on a map of their communities.">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="Why do this: ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;If you need to do a comprehensive social vulnerability assessment such as for a Hazard Mitigation Plan">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="How to do this: ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Using this ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Hyperlink"
			text="social vulnerability table template"
			linkType="externalDOC"
			link="Ch3_social_vulnerability_template_activity_template.docx">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text=", make a blank table on a large piece of paper or white board">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Introduce the activity to the participants, using the instructions in the ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Hyperlink"
			text="workshop facilitator's guide"
			linkType="externalDOC"
			link="Workshop_facilitators_guide.docx">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text=".">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Make sure to explain that the purpose of the activity is not to label certain groups as vulnerable, but to recognize who is most likely to be impacted and how. Recognizing the specific needs of different groups is important to make sure all parts of society are cared for in a disaster.">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Use the major hazards you identified earlier in the chapter as the rows in the table. Refer back to the data and storytelling activities to identify groups for the columns in the table.">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Using one color of sticky notes, add descriptions of the kinds of impacts experienced by different groups.">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- With the whole group, discuss why these impacts happen. What are the underlying systems or historical factors that cause inequities?">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Add notes to the ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Hyperlink"
			text=" Chapter 3 output form"
			linkType="internalStep"
			link="0000005">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
	</container>
<container id="topPanelVBox">
